title: Sunak to urge world leaders to 'move faster' to arm Ukraine as he leads minute's silence on war anniversary
description: Rishi Sunak is to urge fellow world leaders to "move faster" to arm Ukraine's troops as he leads a minute's silence on the one-year anniversary of Russia's invasion.

title: Last factory in Europe producing iconic Meccano toys to close
description: The only factory in Europe dedicated to producing iconic British construction toy brand Meccano is set to close.

title: 'Nowhere else to go': Last resident in badly-damaged block of flats in Ukraine endures extraordinary hardship

title: Johnson calls on UK to 'break the ice' by sending Ukraine fighter jets - and warns China against 'historic mistake'
description: Boris Johnson has said China will be making an "historic mistake" if it supplies Russia with weapons - as he urged the UK to "break the ice" by becoming the first country to supply Ukraine with fighter jets.

title: Student confesses to AirDrop bomb hoax that caused US flight to divert from tarmac, say officials
description: A school pupil has confessed to sending a hoax bomb threat to passengers on a plane using Apple's AirDrop function, US officials have said.

title: TikTok banned from EU Commission phones over cyberattack fears
description: The European Commission has temporarily banned TikTok from its employees' phones over concerns around potential cyberattacks.

title: Girl in Cambodia dies from bird flu
description: An 11-year-old girl from Cambodia has died from bird flu, health officials have said, the first person in the country to die from the infection since 2014.

title: Four arrests at London's Russian embassy as protesters paint massive Ukraine flag on road
description: Four people have been arrested after a huge Ukraine flag was painted on the road outside the Russian embassy in London.

title: Russian 'smash-and-grab' social media operation to influence Ukraine war exposed
description: There has been a sharp increase in the creation of "smash-and-grab" Russian-origin social media accounts since the invasion of Ukraine, Meta's president of global affairs Sir Nick Clegg has said.

title: 'Forever chemicals' found in more than 330 species of wildlife
description: Wildlife across the world - including the UK - is being exposed to pollutants known as "forever chemicals", a study has found.

title: Ukraine would not use Western fighter jets to strike targets in Russia, foreign minister insists
description: Ukraine's foreign minister has insisted that Western fighter jets would not be used by his country to strike targets within Russia.

title: TV journalist, 24, shot dead while reporting at murder scene in Florida
description: A TV journalist has been killed while reporting from the scene of a murder during a shooting spree in Florida that left a total of three people dead and two injured.
